The chain filter → reduce is a very common data processing pattern. Real-world analytics pipelines use this constantly.

```js
const delivered = orders.filter(o => o.status === 'delivered');
const revenue = delivered.reduce((sum, o) => sum + o.total, 0);
const sarahOrders = orders.filter(o => o.user === 'Sarah');

console.log(`Delivered: ${delivered.length} orders, €${revenue.toFixed(2)} revenue. Sarah: ${sarahOrders.length} orders.`);
// Delivered: 2 orders, €324.49 revenue. Sarah: 2 orders.
```

This pattern — filter, then aggregate — is at the core of every reporting and analytics feature you'll ever build.
